        <abstract> 
<p>Thanks THH for his lecture ["On the study of zoology", <hi rend="italic">Lay sermons, addresses and reviews</hi> (1870), pp. 104–31]. Best exposé and classification of the higher objects of natural history he has ever read. On reading and observation.</p> 
            <p>Henrietta’s lack of improvement.</p>
            <p>R. McDonnell’s work on rays and electric organs of fishes.</p>
        </abstract>
